{"parentUuid":"92f9dbac-d61b-418b-972d-adb6277fff85","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"skill_listing","content":"- update-config: Use this skill to configure the Claude Code harness via settings.json. Automated behaviors (\"from now on when X\", \"each time X\", \"whenever X\", \"before/after X\") require hooks configured in settings.json - the harness executes these, not Claude, so memory/preferences cannot fulfill them. Also use for: permissions (\"allow X\", \"add permission\", \"move permission to\"), env vars (\"set X=Y\"), hook troubleshooting, or any changes to settings.json/settings.local.json files. Examples: \"allow npm commands\", \"add bq permission to global settings\", \"move permission to user settings\", \"set DEBUG=true\", \"when claude stops show X\". For simple settings like theme/model, use Config tool.\n- keybindings-help: Use when the user wants to customize keyboard shortcuts, rebind keys, add chord bindings, or modify ~/.claude/keybindings.json. Examples: \"rebind ctrl+s\", \"add a chord shortcut\", \"change the submit key\", \"customize keybindings\".\n- simplify: Review changed code for reuse, quality, and efficiency, then fix any issues found.\n- loop: Run a prompt or slash command on a recurring interval (e.g. /loop 5m /foo). Omit the interval to let the model self-pace. - When the user wants to set up a recurring task, poll for status, or run something repeatedly on an interval (e.g. \"check the deploy every 5 minutes\", \"keep running /babysit-prs\"). Do NOT invoke for one-off tasks.\n- schedule: Create, update, list, or run scheduled remote agents (triggers) that execute on a cron schedule. - When the user wants to schedule a recurring remote agent, set up automated tasks, create a cron job for Claude Code, or manage their scheduled agents/triggers.\n- claude-api: Build, debug, and optimize Claude API / Anthropic SDK apps. Apps built with this skill should include prompt caching.\nTRIGGER when: code imports `anthropic`/`@anthropic-ai/sdk`; user asks for the Claude API, Anthropic SDK, or Managed Agents; user adds/modifies/tunes a Claude feature (caching, thinking, compaction, tool use, batch, files, citations, memory) or model (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku) in a file; questions about prompt caching / cache hit rate in an Anthropic SDK project.\nSKIP: file imports `openai`/other-provider SDK, filename like `*-openai.py`/`*-generic.py`, provider-neutral code, general programming/ML.\n- _sk-read-big-file: Read large files in manageable chunks when they exceed Claude's context limits. Use when working with large log files, data files, or when you get token limit errors reading files.\n- _sk-cross-platform-sh: Review shell scripts for macOS + Linux compatibility. Use when the user asks to check, audit, or fix cross-platform issues in .sh files. Catches BSD vs GNU differences and bash version pitfalls.\n- _sk-linear: Fetch Linear issue details and save to repo\n- _sk-video-analyzer: Extract screenshots and transcribe audio from any video file\n- _sk-branch-ctx: Manage branch-ctx (bctx) - git branch context manager. Use when user asks about branch contexts, _branch/ folder, .bctx/ config, or bctx commands. Auto-invoke when repo has .bctx/ directory.\n- _sk-penpot: Create and edit designs in Penpot via MCP. Use when user asks to create mockups, wireframes, UI designs, or interact with Penpot files.\n- _sk-devpanel: Manage DevPanel VSCode extension config - add tasks, variables, replacements, git excludes. Use when user asks to configure DevPanel or add items to .devpanel/config.jsonc.\n- _sk-sheet: Control Google Sheets - read/write cells, manage sheets, import/export data. Use when user asks to interact with spreadsheets.\n- _sk-afk: Enable AFK mode - registers session for Telegram watch, enables remote communication via HTTP API. Use when user is going AFK and wants to keep interacting via Telegram.\n- _sk-telegram-message: Send Telegram messages to the user via Bot API. Use when Claude Code needs to notify the user about task completion, errors, or any important event.\n- _sk-chrome: Control Chrome browser - take screenshots, extract HTML, click elements, execute JS, get console logs. Use when user asks to interact with browser tabs.\n- _sk-loom-download: Download Loom videos to local filesystem\n- simple-skill: A minimal skill for testing. Just responds with a confirmation message.\n- _cm:research:research-topic: Research Topic\n- _cm:research:analyse-repo: Analyse Repo\n- _cm:gh:repo-naming: Repo Naming\n- _cm:gh:create-repo-readme: Create Repo Readme\n- _cm:bc:gh-resolve-comment: Resolve PR Comment\n- _cm:bc:bb-subticket-focus: Focus Subticket\n- _cm:bc:explain: Explain Branch\n- _cm:bc:read: Read Context\n- _cm:bc:linear-fetch-info: Fetch Linear Info\n- _cm:bc:bb-subticket-add: Add Subticket\n- _cm:bc:bb-subticket-resolve: Resolve Subticket\n- _cm:bc:gh-fetch-comments: Fetch PR Comments\n- _cm:bc:add: Add Context\n- _cm:bc:bb-subticket-list: List Subtickets\n- _cm:bc:update: Update Context\n- _cm:bc:commit: Commit Context\n- _cm:docs:gen-docs: Gen Docs\n- _cm:docs:align-docs: Align Docs\n- _cm:sdd:implement: Implement\n- _cm:sdd:validate: Validate\n- _cm:sdd:plan: Plan\n- _cm:sdd:brainstorm: Brainstorm\n- frontend-design:frontend-design: Create distinctive, production-grade frontend interfaces with high design quality. Use this skill when the user asks to build web components, pages, or applications. Generates creative, polished code that avoids generic AI aesthetics.\n- init: Initialize a new CLAUDE.md file with codebase documentation\n- review: Review a pull request\n- security-review: Complete a security review of the pending changes on the current branch","skillCount":45,"isInitial":true},"type":"attachment","uuid":"508e7ccc-9480-4438-96bb-c5031b3a147f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T00:49:24.360Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/Users/lucas/_custom/repos/github_lucasvtiradentes/pretty-sessions/.sandbox/notebook-edit","sessionId":"c90beb8c-d7bb